{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":874,"text":"So there's a lot of valid\nconcern these days"},{"time":3050,"text":"that our technology is getting so smart"},{"time":5279,"text":"that we've put ourselves\non the path to a jobless future."},{"time":9682,"text":"And I think the example\nof a self-driving car"},{"time":11858,"text":"is actually the easiest one to see."},{"time":13556,"text":"So these are going to be fantastic\nfor all kinds of different reasons."},{"time":16908,"text":"But did you know that \"driver\"\nis actually the most common job"},{"time":20370,"text":"in 29 of the 50 US states?"},{"time":23042,"text":"What's going to happen to these jobs\nwhen we're no longer driving our cars"},{"time":26544,"text":"or cooking our food"},{"time":27733,"text":"or even diagnosing our own diseases?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30675,"text":"Well, a recent study\nfrom Forrester Research"},{"time":33076,"text":"goes so far to predict\nthat 25 million jobs"},{"time":36263,"text":"might disappear over the next 10 years."},{"time":39393,"text":"To put that in perspective,"},{"time":40906,"text":"that's three times as many jobs lost\nin the aftermath of the financial crisis."},{"time":46606,"text":"And it's not just blue-collar jobs\nthat are at risk."},{"time":49728,"text":"On Wall Street and across Silicon Valley,\nwe are seeing tremendous gains"},{"time":53179,"text":"in the quality of analysis\nand decision-making"},{"time":55385,"text":"because of machine learning."},{"time":57063,"text":"So even the smartest, highest-paid people\nwill be affected by this change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61714,"text":"What's clear is that no matter\nwhat your job is,"},{"time":64408,"text":"at least some, if not all of your work,"},{"time":66404,"text":"is going to be done by a robot\nor software in the next few years."},{"time":70918,"text":"And that's exactly why people\nlike Mark Zuckerberg and Bill Gates"},{"time":74013,"text":"are talking about the need for\ngovernment-funded minimum income levels."},{"time":77425,"text":"But if our politicians can't agree\non things like health care"},{"time":80791,"text":"or even school lunches,"},{"time":82094,"text":"I just don't see a path\nwhere they'll find consensus"},{"time":84548,"text":"on something as big and as expensive\nas universal basic life income."},{"time":88616,"text":"Instead, I think the response\nneeds to be led by us in industry."},{"time":92285,"text":"We have to recognize\nthe change that's ahead of us"},{"time":94833,"text":"and start to design the new kinds of jobs"},{"time":96832,"text":"that will still be relevant\nin the age of robotics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100899,"text":"The good news is that we have\nfaced down and recovered"},{"time":103676,"text":"two mass extinctions of jobs before."},{"time":106523,"text":"From 1870 to 1970,"},{"time":108757,"text":"the percent of American workers\nbased on farms fell by 90 percent,"},{"time":113189,"text":"and then again from 1950 to 2010,"},{"time":115758,"text":"the percent of Americans\nworking in factories"},{"time":117925,"text":"fell by 75 percent."},{"time":120570,"text":"The challenge we face this time,\nhowever, is one of time."},{"time":123548,"text":"We had a hundred years\nto move from farms to factories,"},{"time":126586,"text":"and then 60 years to fully build out\na service economy."},{"time":129678,"text":"The rate of change today"},{"time":131027,"text":"suggests that we may only have\n10 or 15 years to adjust,"},{"time":134025,"text":"and if we don't react fast enough,"},{"time":135752,"text":"that means by the time\ntoday's elementary-school students"},{"time":138532,"text":"are college-aged,"},{"time":140441,"text":"we could be living\nin a world that's robotic,"},{"time":142606,"text":"largely unemployed and stuck\nin kind of un-great depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147797,"text":"But I don't think it has to be this way."},{"time":149760,"text":"You see, I work in innovation,"},{"time":151484,"text":"and part of my job is to shape how\nlarge companies apply new technologies."},{"time":156265,"text":"Certainly some of these technologies"},{"time":158084,"text":"are even specifically designed\nto replace human workers."},{"time":161615,"text":"But I believe that if we start\ntaking steps right now"},{"time":164565,"text":"to change the nature of work,"},{"time":166410,"text":"we can not only create environments\nwhere people love coming to work"},{"time":170320,"text":"but also generate\nthe innovation that we need"},{"time":172462,"text":"to replace the millions of jobs\nthat will be lost to technology."},{"time":176532,"text":"I believe that the key\nto preventing our jobless future"},{"time":180355,"text":"is to rediscover what makes us human,"},{"time":182725,"text":"and to create a new generation\nof human-centered jobs"},{"time":185707,"text":"that allow us to unlock\nthe hidden talents and passions"},{"time":188337,"text":"that we carry with us every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192151,"text":"But first, I think\nit's important to recognize"},{"time":194318,"text":"that we brought this problem on ourselves."},{"time":196494,"text":"And it's not just because, you know,\nwe are the one building the robots."},{"time":200507,"text":"But even though most jobs\nleft the factory decades ago,"},{"time":203715,"text":"we still hold on to this factory mindset"},{"time":205676,"text":"of standardization and de-skilling."},{"time":208525,"text":"We still define jobs\naround procedural tasks"},{"time":210900,"text":"and then pay people for the number\nof hours that they perform these tasks."},{"time":214412,"text":"We've created narrow job definitions"},{"time":216192,"text":"like cashier, loan processor\nor taxi driver"},{"time":219456,"text":"and then asked people\nto form entire careers"},{"time":221963,"text":"around these singular tasks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224251,"text":"These choices have left us with\nactually two dangerous side effects."},{"time":227808,"text":"The first is that these\nnarrowly defined jobs"},{"time":230582,"text":"will be the first\nto be displaced by robots,"},{"time":233029,"text":"because single-task robots\nare just the easiest kinds to build."},{"time":236781,"text":"But second, we have accidentally made it"},{"time":239198,"text":"so that millions of workers\naround the world"},{"time":241350,"text":"have unbelievably boring working lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244057,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":246427,"text":"Let's take the example\nof a call center agent."},{"time":248853,"text":"Over the last few decades,\nwe brag about lower operating costs"},{"time":251880,"text":"because we've taken most\nof the need for brainpower"},{"time":254331,"text":"out of the person\nand put it into the system."},{"time":256499,"text":"For most of their day,\nthey click on screens,"},{"time":259044,"text":"they read scripts."},{"time":261487,"text":"They act more like machines than humans."},{"time":265278,"text":"And unfortunately,\nover the next few years,"},{"time":267418,"text":"as our technology gets more advanced,"},{"time":269301,"text":"they, along with people\nlike clerks and bookkeepers,"},{"time":271909,"text":"will see the vast majority\nof their work disappear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275495,"text":"To counteract this,\nwe have to start creating new jobs"},{"time":278223,"text":"that are less centered\non the tasks that a person does"},{"time":280786,"text":"and more focused on the skills\nthat a person brings to work."},{"time":284389,"text":"For example, robots are great\nat repetitive and constrained work,"},{"time":287800,"text":"but human beings have an amazing ability"},{"time":289773,"text":"to bring together\ncapability with creativity"},{"time":292076,"text":"when faced with problems\nthat we've never seen before."},{"time":295122,"text":"It's when every day\nbrings a little bit of a surprise"},{"time":298126,"text":"that we have designed work for humans"},{"time":300154,"text":"and not for robots."},{"time":302130,"text":"Our entrepreneurs and engineers\nalready live in this world,"},{"time":305052,"text":"but so do our nurses and our plumbers"},{"time":307668,"text":"and our therapists."},{"time":309749,"text":"You know, it's the nature\nof too many companies and organizations"},{"time":312830,"text":"to just ask people to come to work\nand do your job."},{"time":316544,"text":"But if you work is better done by a robot,"},{"time":318754,"text":"or your decisions better made by an AI,"},{"time":321575,"text":"what are you supposed to be doing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324013,"text":"Well, I think for the manager,"},{"time":326521,"text":"we need to realistically think about\nthe tasks that will be disappearing"},{"time":329942,"text":"over the next few years"},{"time":331117,"text":"and start planning for more meaningful,\nmore valuable work that should replace it."},{"time":335013,"text":"We need to create environments"},{"time":336466,"text":"where both human beings and robots thrive."},{"time":338729,"text":"I say, let's give more work to the robots,"},{"time":341289,"text":"and let's start with the work\nthat we absolutely hate doing."},{"time":345428,"text":"Here, robot,"},{"time":346616,"text":"process this painfully idiotic report."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348491,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":349938,"text":"And move this box. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351387,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353110,"text":"And for the human beings,"},{"time":354663,"text":"we should follow the advice from Harry\nDavis at the University of Chicago."},{"time":358241,"text":"He says we have to make it so that people\ndon't leave too much of themselves"},{"time":361914,"text":"in the trunk of their car."},{"time":363269,"text":"I mean, human beings\nare amazing on weekends."},{"time":366182,"text":"Think about the people that you know\nand what they do on Saturdays."},{"time":369350,"text":"They're artists, carpenters,\nchefs and athletes."},{"time":373086,"text":"But on Monday, they're back\nto being Junior HR Specialist"},{"time":377006,"text":"and Systems Analyst 3."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379129,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":382934,"text":"You know, these narrow job titles\nnot only sound boring,"},{"time":386276,"text":"but they're actually\na subtle encouragement"},{"time":388396,"text":"for people to make narrow\nand boring job contributions."},{"time":391460,"text":"But I've seen firsthand\nthat when you invite people to be more,"},{"time":394600,"text":"they can amaze us\nwith how much more they can be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398327,"text":"A few years ago,\nI was working at a large bank"},{"time":400584,"text":"that was trying to bring more innovation\ninto its company culture."},{"time":403704,"text":"So my team and I designed\na prototyping contest"},{"time":406069,"text":"that invited anyone to build\nanything that they wanted."},{"time":409704,"text":"We were actually trying to figure out"},{"time":411561,"text":"whether or not\nthe primary limiter to innovation"},{"time":413853,"text":"was a lack of ideas or a lack of talent,"},{"time":416367,"text":"and it turns out it was neither one."},{"time":418252,"text":"It was an empowerment problem."},{"time":420698,"text":"And the results\nof the program were amazing."},{"time":424378,"text":"We started by inviting\npeople to reenvision"},{"time":426779,"text":"what it is they could bring to a team."},{"time":428918,"text":"This contest was not only a chance\nto build anything that you wanted"},{"time":432680,"text":"but also be anything that you wanted."},{"time":435040,"text":"And when people were no longer\nlimited by their day-to-day job titles,"},{"time":438350,"text":"they felt free to bring all kinds\nof different skills and talents"},{"time":441521,"text":"to the problems\nthat they were trying to solve."},{"time":444031,"text":"We saw technology people being designers,\nmarketing people being architects,"},{"time":447965,"text":"and even finance people showing off\ntheir ability to write jokes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451607,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452781,"text":"We ran this program twice,"},{"time":454210,"text":"and each time more than 400 people\nbrought their unexpected talents to work"},{"time":458030,"text":"and solved problems that they had been\nwanting to solve for years."},{"time":461490,"text":"Collectively, they created\nmillions of dollars of value,"},{"time":464533,"text":"building things like a better\ntouch-tone system for call centers,"},{"time":469122,"text":"easier desktop tools for branches"},{"time":470814,"text":"and even a thank you card system"},{"time":472363,"text":"that has become a cornerstone\nof the employee working experience."},{"time":475701,"text":"Over the course of the eight weeks,"},{"time":477528,"text":"people flexed muscles that they never\ndreamed of using at work."},{"time":482353,"text":"People learned new skills,"},{"time":483954,"text":"they met new people,"},{"time":486346,"text":"and at the end, somebody\npulled me aside and said,"},{"time":489163,"text":"\"I have to tell you,"},{"time":490756,"text":"the last few weeks has been\none of the most intense,"},{"time":493556,"text":"hardest working experiences\nof my entire life,"},{"time":496859,"text":"but not one second of it felt like work.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":500080,"text":"And that's the key."},{"time":501402,"text":"For those few weeks, people\ngot to be creators and innovators."},{"time":506811,"text":"They had been dreaming of solutions"},{"time":508502,"text":"to problems that had been\nbugging them for years,"},{"time":511010,"text":"and this was a chance to turn\nthose dreams into a reality."},{"time":514669,"text":"And that dreaming is an important part\nof what separates us from machines."},{"time":519135,"text":"For now, our machines\ndo not get frustrated,"},{"time":522177,"text":"they do not get annoyed,"},{"time":523608,"text":"and they certainly don't imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525892,"text":"But we, as human beings --"},{"time":527615,"text":"we feel pain,"},{"time":528846,"text":"we get frustrated."},{"time":530270,"text":"And it's when we're most annoyed\nand most curious"},{"time":533410,"text":"that we're motivated to dig\ninto a problem and create change."},{"time":537546,"text":"Our imaginations are the birthplace\nof new products, new services,"},{"time":541480,"text":"and even new industries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543476,"text":"I believe that the jobs of the future"},{"time":545302,"text":"will come from the minds of people"},{"time":547039,"text":"who today we call\nanalysts and specialists,"},{"time":549779,"text":"but only if we give them the freedom\nand protection that they need to grow"},{"time":553281,"text":"into becoming explorers and inventors."},{"time":556714,"text":"If we really want to robot-proof our jobs,"},{"time":558881,"text":"we, as leaders, need\nto get out of the mindset"},{"time":561140,"text":"of telling people what to do"},{"time":562994,"text":"and instead start asking them\nwhat problems they're inspired to solve"},{"time":566839,"text":"and what talents\nthey want to bring to work."},{"time":569681,"text":"Because when you can bring\nyour Saturday self to work on Wednesdays,"},{"time":573148,"text":"you'll look forward to Mondays more,"},{"time":575166,"text":"and those feelings\nthat we have about Mondays"},{"time":577872,"text":"are part of what makes us human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580467,"text":"And as we redesign work\nfor an era of intelligent machines,"},{"time":583499,"text":"I invite you all to work alongside me"},{"time":585739,"text":"to bring more humanity\nto our working lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588405,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589580,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}